.DT
add_exit_type
$MUDNAME$ Creator Help
add_exit_type

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
add_exit_type -  This method adds an exit type to the current list of available exit types.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int add_exit_type(string type,
mixed message,
mixed obvious,
int size,
mixed func)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^type%^RESET%^ - the name of the exit type
%^BOLD%^message%^RESET%^ - the message to display when going through the exit
%^BOLD%^obvious%^RESET%^ - if the exit is obvious or not
%^BOLD%^size%^RESET%^ - the size of the exit (used for heigh restrictions)
%^BOLD%^func%^RESET%^ - the function to call when using the exit
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
1 if successfuly added, 0 if not
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/handlers/room_handler.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method adds an exit type to the current list of available exit types.
This is used when the room handler is setup to add all the used exit
types.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
remove_exit_type()

.EP

